SIMPLE: presentation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presentation
<hw>Pres`en*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praesentatio</ets> a showing, representation: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧sentation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
presenting, or the state of being presented; a setting forth; an
offering; bestowal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Prayers are sometimes a <qex>presentation</qex> of mere
desires.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> Hence, <def>exhibition; representation; display;
appearance; semblance; show.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Under the <qex>presentation</qex> of the shoots his wit.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is presented or given; a present; a gift,
<as>as, the picture was a <ex>presentation</ex></as>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The act of offering a clergyman
to the bishop or ordinary for institution in a benefice; the right of
presenting a clergyman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If the bishop admits the patron's <qex>presentation</qex>, the
clerk so admitted is next to be instituted by him.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The particular position of the
child during labor relatively to the passage though which it is to be
brought forth; -- specifically designated by the part which first
appears at the mouth of the uterus; <as>as, a breech
<ex>presentation</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Presentation copy</b></col>, <cd>a copy of a book,
engraving, etc., presented to some one by the author or artist, as a
token of regard.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presentative</ent>⟦br⟧
